---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro'
---
<DocsLayout title="License & Activation" description="How to activate, manage, and understand your Ravenburst license.">
  <h1 class="text-4xl font-serif font-bold text-rb-text mb-2">License & Activation</h1>
  <p class="text-rb-muted mb-10">Everything about your Ravenburst license.</p>

  <div class="space-y-10 text-sm text-rb-muted leading-relaxed">

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Free Trial</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">Ravenburst includes a <strong class="text-rb-text">7-day free trial</strong>. No account, no credit card required. On first launch, the app registers your machine with our server and starts the trial automatically.</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>The trial countdown is shown in the status bar</li>
        <li>All features are available during the trial</li>
        <li>If you're offline when you first launch, the trial starts once you connect</li>
        <li>When the trial expires, writing and reading continue — only saving and exporting are paused until you activate</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Activating Your License</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">After purchasing at <a href="/pricing" class="text-rb-accent">ravenburst.com/pricing</a>, you'll receive an activation code by email within a few minutes.</p>
      <ol class="space-y-2 list-decimal list-inside">
        <li>Open Ravenburst</li>
        <li>Go to <strong class="text-rb-text">Help → Enter Activation Code</strong></li>
        <li>Enter the email address you used to purchase</li>
        <li>Paste your activation code</li>
        <li>Click <strong class="text-rb-text">Activate</strong></li>
      </ol>
      <p class="mt-3">Activation requires an internet connection to register your device.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Multiple Devices</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">One license covers <strong class="text-rb-text">up to 3 devices</strong>. If you get a new computer, deactivate your old one first to free up a slot.</p>
      <p>Go to <strong class="text-rb-text">Help → Deactivate License on This Device</strong>. You can then activate on your new machine using the same code.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Lost Your Activation Code?</h2>
      <p>Email <a href="mailto:support@ravenburst.com" class="text-rb-accent">support@ravenburst.com</a> with the email address you used to purchase. We'll resend your code within 48 hours.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Offline Use</h2>
      <p class="mb-3">Once activated, Ravenburst works almost entirely offline. The only things that require internet are:</p>
      <ul class="space-y-1 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>Initial trial registration</li>
        <li>Activating your license code</li>
        <li>The 30-day license heartbeat (a silent background check — if offline, the app continues normally)</li>
        <li>Claude AI analysis (if you use the Claude option)</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Upgrades</h2>
      <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
        <li>Your license includes <strong class="text-rb-text">free updates through v2</strong> — all patches and minor versions at no cost</li>
        <li>Future major versions (v3+) will be available at a discounted upgrade price (~$10–15)</li>
        <li>You are never forced to upgrade — your current version keeps working</li>
        <li>Kickstarter backers receive free updates through v3</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-rb-text mb-4">Refunds</h2>
      <p>We offer a full refund within 30 days of purchase, no questions asked. Email <a href="mailto:support@ravenburst.com" class="text-rb-accent">support@ravenburst.com</a>. Upon refund, your activation code will be deactivated and the app will revert to an expired state.</p>
    </section>

  </div>
</DocsLayout>
